Generate a complete 30-Day Faith & Family Devotional in structured JSON format.

For each of the 30 days, provide:

{
  "days": [
    {
      "day_number": 1,
      "theme": "One word theme",
      "scripture_reference": "Book Chapter:Verse",
      "scripture_text": "Full verse text",
      "devotional": "200-250 words: open with a relatable family/marriage scenario, connect to scripture, offer a practical insight, close with hope",
      "reflection_questions": ["3 questions for individual or couple discussion"],
      "prayer": "3-4 sentences, personal and specific to the day's theme",
      "daily_challenge": "One concrete action to take today"
    }
  ]
}

Week 1 (Days 1-7): Foundation — establishing faith rhythms in family life
Week 2 (Days 8-14): Marriage — deepening connection through shared faith
Week 3 (Days 15-21): Parenting — raising children with grace and intention
Week 4 (Days 22-30): Faith in Hard Times — holding on when life gets heavy

Requirements:
- Use varied books of the Bible (not just Psalms and Proverbs)
- Tone: Warm, genuine, practical. Like a trusted friend, not a theologian.
- Avoid clichés. Be specific and real.
- Each devotional should stand alone but also flow as a journey
- Reflection questions should provoke real thought, not yes/no answers
- Prayers should be conversational with God, not formal
- Challenges should be doable in under 10 minutes

Output ONLY valid JSON.
